article.headline: St. Francis, Pa. 94, Lock Haven 60
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. (AP) -- Freshman Devin Sweetney finished with 20 points and nine rebounds, and five players scored in double figures for St. Francis, Pa., in a 94-60 win over Division II Lock Haven on Saturday night. Center J.R. Enright, who missed most of last season with a broken foot, had 19 points and 12 rebounds in the opener for St. Francis, which is coming off a 4-24 season. Chris Berry and Cale Nelson each scored 13, and sub Grant Surprenant added 12. Billy Arre scored 22 points to lead Lock Haven (0-2). James Chappell added 15 points and Justin Wilson nine. St. Francis never trailed and built a 48-28 lead by the break. The Red Flash shot 59.3 percent in the second half and extended their lead to 36 points. The Red Flash also dominated the smaller Bald Eagles, building a 44-24 rebounding edge and scoring 26 points off 19 turnovers.
